Functional Design Document (FDD)

Project Title: Enhanced AppDynamics BT Onboarding for Multi-Datacenter KPI Fetching

Version: 1.0
Date: [Enter Current Date]
Authors: [Your Team/Name]

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

1. Introduction
    *   This document describes the functional design for the "Enhanced AppDynamics BT Onboarding for Multi-Datacenter KPI Fetching" feature. It details how the user (SRE) will interact with the system to configure AppDynamics Business Transactions (BTs) that source KPIs from multiple datacenters.
    *   This FDD builds upon the requirements outlined in the PRD.

2. User Roles & Goals
    *   User: Site Reliability Engineer (SRE) or Application Operations team member.
    *   Goal: To easily and accurately onboard a new AppDynamics BT or update an existing one to fetch KPIs from multiple datacenters without manually entering multiple full REST URLs.

3. Functional Overview
    The SRE onboarding page for BTs will be modified. When "AppDynamics" is selected as the KPI backend source, new UI elements will allow the user to specify if the BT is multi-datacenter. If so, they will provide a base metric path and select the relevant datacenters from a predefined list.

4. Detailed Functional Specifications

    4.1. BT Onboarding/Editing Form - AppDynamics Source
        *   **Existing Fields:** (Assume fields like "BT Name", "KPIs", "Description", "Owner", etc., remain as is).
        *   **KPI Backend Selection:**
            *   Dropdown: "Select KPI Backend" (Options: Splunk, AppDynamics, etc.)
            *   Current Behavior: When "AppDynamics" is selected, a field for "AppDynamics REST URL" is typically shown.

        *   **New/Modified Behavior when "AppDynamics" is selected:**
            1.  **"Configure for Multiple Datacenters?" Checkbox/Toggle:**
                *   Label: "Fetch KPIs from multiple datacenters?"
                *   Type: Checkbox or Toggle Switch.
                *   Default: Unchecked / Off.

            2.  **If "Fetch KPIs from multiple datacenters?" is UNCHECKED (Legacy/Single DC Mode):**
                *   Display the existing input field:
                    *   Label: "AppDynamics REST URL"
                    *   Input Type: Text field.
                    *   Description/Tooltip: "Enter the full AppDynamics REST API URL to fetch KPIs."
                    *   Behavior: Functions as currently implemented for single AppDynamics URLs.

            3.  **If "Fetch KPIs from multiple datacenters?" is CHECKED (New Multi-DC Mode):**
                *   Hide the "AppDynamics REST URL" input field.
                *   Display the following new input fields:
                    *   **Field 1: "AppDynamics Base Metric Path"**
                        *   Label: "AppDynamics Base Metric Path"
                        *   Input Type: Text field.
                        *   Description/Tooltip: "Enter the AppDynamics metric path common across datacenters. Example: MyGreatApp/tiers/MyTier/Business%20Transaction%20Performance/BTs/MyBTName/KPIs/Average%20Response%20Time%20(ms). Do NOT include the controller base URL (e.g., https://...). The system will append this to the correct datacenter controller URL."
                        *   Validation: Required. Must not be empty. Should ideally not start with http/https.
                    *   **Field 2: "Target Datacenters"**
                        *   Label: "Select Target Datacenters"
                        *   Input Type: Multi-select dropdown list or a list of checkboxes.
                        *   Options: The list of datacenters will be populated from a system-defined configuration (e.g., "DC1", "DC2", "US-EAST-1", "EU-WEST-1").
                        *   Description/Tooltip: "Select all datacenters from which KPIs for this BT should be fetched."
                        *   Validation: At least one datacenter must be selected.

    4.2. User Flows

        4.2.1. User Onboards a New Multi-Datacenter AppDynamics BT
            1.  User navigates to the "Onboard New BT" page.
            2.  User fills in common BT details (Name, Description, etc.).
            3.  User selects "AppDynamics" from the "Select KPI Backend" dropdown.
            4.  The "Fetch KPIs from multiple datacenters?" checkbox appears (unchecked by default).
            5.  User CHECKS the "Fetch KPIs from multiple datacenters?" checkbox.
            6.  The "AppDynamics REST URL" field is hidden (or disabled).
            7.  The "AppDynamics Base Metric Path" input field and "Select Target Datacenters" multi-select dropdown become visible and enabled.
            8.  User enters a valid base metric path into the "AppDynamics Base Metric Path" field.
            9.  User selects one or more datacenters from the "Select Target Datacenters" list.
            10. User clicks "Save" or "Submit."
            11. System validates inputs:
                *   If validation fails (e.g., base metric path empty, no datacenters selected), an appropriate error message is displayed next to the relevant field(s), and the form is not submitted.
                *   If validation passes, the configuration is saved, and the user is redirected to a confirmation page or BT details page.

        4.2.2. User Onboards a New Single-Datacenter AppDynamics BT (Existing Behavior)
            1.  User navigates to the "Onboard New BT" page.
            2.  User fills in common BT details.
            3.  User selects "AppDynamics" from "Select KPI Backend."
            4.  User LEAVES "Fetch KPIs from multiple datacenters?" UNCHECKED.
            5.  The "AppDynamics REST URL" field is visible and enabled.
            6.  User enters the full AppDynamics REST URL.
            7.  User clicks "Save" or "Submit."
            8.  System validates and saves (current behavior).

        4.2.3. User Edits an Existing BT
            *   If editing an old AppDynamics BT (configured with a single full URL): The form loads with "Fetch KPIs from multiple datacenters?" UNCHECKED and the "AppDynamics REST URL" field populated. The SRE can choose to switch to the multi-DC mode.
            *   If editing a new AppDynamics BT (configured with multi-DC mode): The form loads with "Fetch KPIs from multiple datacenters?" CHECKED, the "AppDynamics Base Metric Path" populated, and the previously selected datacenters highlighted in the "Select Target Datacenters" list.

    4.3. Error Handling and Validation Messages (Examples)
        *   On "AppDynamics Base Metric Path" field:
            *   If empty when multi-DC is checked: "Base Metric Path is required."
            *   If it looks like a full URL: "Please enter only the metric path, not the full controller URL." (Optional, helpful validation)
        *   On "Select Target Datacenters" field:
            *   If none selected when multi-DC is checked: "At least one datacenter must be selected."
        *   General form submission error (if backend save fails): "An error occurred while saving the BT configuration. Please try again."

    4.4. Data Display (Assumption)
        *   This FDD assumes that the existing KPI display mechanism in the portal can handle and correctly attribute KPIs to their source datacenter when the backend provides this information (as it already does for Splunk). No changes to the display screens are detailed in this FDD, but consistency is expected.

5. Non-Functional Requirements (from User Perspective)
    *   Performance: The onboarding form should remain responsive. Selecting datacenters should be quick.
    *   Usability: The new options for AppDynamics multi-DC configuration should be intuitive and easy to understand for SREs. Tooltips and clear labels are important.
    *   Accessibility: Standard web accessibility guidelines should be followed for new UI elements.

6. Out of Scope (for this FDD, related to UI/Functionality)
    *   Admin interface for managing the list of datacenters (this FDD assumes the list is available to the form).
    *   Automatic detection/suggestion of base metric paths or datacenters.

7. Open Questions/Points for UX Review
    *   Is a multi-select dropdown or a list of checkboxes better for "Select Target Datacenters"? (Consider the typical number of datacenters).
    *   Clarity of labels and tooltip text for the new fields – requires SRE feedback.

