Product Requirements Document (PRD)

Project Title: Enhanced AppDynamics BT Onboarding for Multi-Datacenter KPI Fetching

Version: 1.0
Date: [Enter Current Date]
Authors: [Your Team/Name]

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

1. Introduction & Purpose
    *   Current Situation: Our SRE onboarding portal allows users (primarily SREs) to onboard application Business Transactions (BTs) by specifying details like name, KPIs, and how to fetch these KPIs from backend systems like Splunk or AppDynamics. While Splunk queries are typically designed to return KPIs per datacenter from a single query, AppDynamics KPI fetching currently requires SREs to manually input separate REST URLs for each datacenter if a BT spans multiple datacenters.
    *   Problem: This manual input of multiple AppDynamics URLs is cumbersome, error-prone, time-consuming, and creates an inconsistent user experience compared to the more streamlined Splunk onboarding process.
    *   Goal: To improve the SRE onboarding experience for AppDynamics-backed BTs by enabling a simplified, unified method for configuring KPI fetching across multiple datacenters, similar to the ease of use provided for Splunk.

2. Target Users
    *   Site Reliability Engineers (SREs)
    *   Application Operations teams responsible for monitoring and onboarding BTs into the portal.

3. User Needs & Pain Points Addressed
    *   Need for Efficiency: SREs need to onboard BTs quickly and without repetitive manual data entry.
    *   Need for Accuracy: Reduce the likelihood of typos or incorrect URLs when configuring multiple AppDynamics endpoints.
    *   Need for Consistency: Provide a more consistent onboarding experience regardless of whether the backend is Splunk or AppDynamics for multi-datacenter scenarios.
    *   Current Pain: Frustration with manually identifying and entering multiple AppDynamics URLs for each datacenter. Increased chance of missing a datacenter or entering an incorrect URL.

4. Proposed Solution (High-Level)
    Modify the SRE onboarding page for BTs. When "AppDynamics" is selected as the KPI backend, instead of requiring multiple individual REST URL inputs for multi-datacenter applications, the system will allow users to:
    *   Specify a base AppDynamics REST URL component (e.g., metric path).
    *   Indicate the datacenters from which KPIs for this BT should be fetched.
    The backend system will then be responsible for constructing and executing the necessary API calls to each specified AppDynamics instance for the relevant datacenters.

5. User Stories
    *   US1: As an SRE, I want to onboard an AppDynamics BT that spans multiple datacenters by providing a single base configuration and selecting the relevant datacenters, so that I don't have to manually input multiple REST URLs and can reduce configuration errors.
    *   US2: As an SRE, when configuring an AppDynamics BT for multiple datacenters, I want the system to guide me in specifying the datacenter-specific information clearly, so that the configuration is straightforward.
    *   US3: As an SRE, I expect the portal to automatically fetch KPIs from all specified datacenters for an AppDynamics BT configured using the new method, so that I get a complete view of my application's health without manual intervention for each DC.
    *   US4: As an SRE, I want the process for configuring multi-datacenter AppDynamics BTs to feel as intuitive and efficient as the current process for multi-datacenter Splunk BTs.

6. Key Features/Requirements
    *   FR1: Modified UI for AppDynamics Source:
        *   When "AppDynamics" is selected as the backend, the UI must provide an option to indicate that the BT spans multiple datacenters.
        *   If multi-datacenter is indicated:
            *   Allow input for a *base* AppDynamics metric path (e.g., "MyApplication/path/to/metric").
            *   Provide a mechanism for the SRE to select/specify the relevant datacenters (e.g., multi-select dropdown from a pre-defined list).
    *   FR2: Datacenter Configuration (Backend Support):
        *   The system must have a way to map a "datacenter" selection to a specific AppDynamics instance base URL (managed via system configuration).
    *   FR3: Backend Logic for Multi-DC KPI Fetching:
        *   The backend service must dynamically construct the specific AppDynamics REST URL for each selected datacenter and execute API calls.
        *   Aggregate or present per-datacenter KPIs consistently with Splunk.
    *   FR4: Validation:
        *   Input validation for new AppDynamics configuration fields.
        *   Validation that selected datacenters are valid.
    *   FR5: Backward Compatibility:
        *   Existing AppDynamics BTs (single URL) must continue to function. This enhancement applies to new/edited BTs opting into the multi-DC mode.

7. Success Metrics
    *   Reduction in average time to onboard a multi-datacenter AppDynamics BT.
    *   Decrease in configuration errors/support tickets for AppDynamics BT onboarding.
    *   Positive qualitative feedback from SREs (ease of use, efficiency).
    *   Adoption rate of the new feature for new AppDynamics BTs.

8. Scope
    *   In Scope:
        *   UI modifications to the BT onboarding page for AppDynamics source.
        *   Backend changes for multi-DC AppDynamics configuration and KPI fetching.
        *   Mechanism for SREs to specify target datacenters.
    *   Out of Scope (for this iteration):
        *   Changes to Splunk onboarding.
        *   Auto-discovery of datacenters for an AppDynamics application.
        *   Fundamental changes to KPI display (assuming current display supports per-DC data).
        *   Admin interface for managing datacenter-to-AppDynamics URL mappings (assumed system config for now).
        *   Automated migration of old AppDynamics configurations.

9. Assumptions
    *   A predefined list of datacenters is available/configurable in the system.
    *   A consistent pattern or manageable mapping exists for AppDynamics controller base URLs per datacenter.
    *   The AppDynamics REST API *metric path* for a given KPI is largely the same across datacenters.

10. Open Questions/Further Discussion Points
    *   How exactly will the mapping between "datacenter" and its AppDynamics controller URL be managed? (PRD assumes system config, TDD details this).
    *   How to handle slight metric path variations per DC (if they exist)? (PRD defers this).
    *   Error handling presentation for individual DC AppDynamics calls.

